==Events== * [[215 BC]] &ndash; [[Temple of Venus Erycina|A temple]] is built on the [[Capitoline Hill]] dedicated to [[Venus Erycina]] to commemorate the [[Roman Republic|Roman]] defeat at [[Battle of Lake Trasimene|Lake Trasimene]]. * [[599]] &ndash; Maya king [[Scroll Serpent|Uneh Chan]] of [[Calakmul]] attacks rival city-state [[Palenque]] in southern Mexico, defeating queen [[Yohl Ik'nal]] and sacking the city. * [[711]] &ndash; [[Dagobert III]] succeeds his father King [[Childebert III]] as [[King of the Franks]]. * [[1014]] &ndash; [[Battle of Clontarf]]: High King of Ireland [[Brian Boru]] defeats [[Viking]] invaders, but is killed in battle. * [[1016]] &ndash; [[Edmund Ironside]] succeeds his father [[Æthelred the Unready]] as King of England. * [[1343]] &ndash; [[St. George's Night Uprising]] commences in the [[Danish Estonia#Duchy of Estonia|Duchy of Estonia]]. * [[1348]] &ndash; The founding of the [[Order of the Garter]] by King [[Edward III of England|Edward III]] is announced on [[Saint George|St. George's Day]]. * [[1516]] &ndash; The Bayerische [[Reinheitsgebot]] (regarding the ingredients of beer) is signed in [[Ingolstadt]]. * [[1521]] &ndash; [[Battle of Villalar]]: [[Charles V, Holy Roman Emperor|King Charles I of Spain]] defeats the [[Revolt of the Comuneros|Comuneros]]. * [[1635]] &ndash; The first public school in the United States, [[Boston Latin School]], is founded in [[Boston]]. * [[1655]] &ndash; The [[Siege of Santo Domingo (1655)|Siege of Santo Domingo]] begins during the [[Anglo-Spanish War (1654–60)|Anglo-Spanish War]], and fails seven days later. * [[1660]] &ndash; [[Treaty of Oliva]] is established between Sweden and Poland. * [[1661]] &ndash; King [[Charles II of England]], Scotland and Ireland is crowned in [[Westminster Abbey]]. * [[1815]] &ndash; [[Second Serbian Uprising|The Second Serbian Uprising]]: A second phase of the national revolution of the Serbs against the [[Ottoman Empire]], erupts shortly after the annexation of the country to the Ottoman Empire. * [[1879]] &ndash; Fire burns down the second main building and dome of the [[University of Notre Dame]], which prompts the construction of the third, and current, [[Main Building (University of Notre Dame)|Main Building]] with its golden dome. * [[1914]] &ndash; First [[baseball]] game at [[History of Wrigley Field|Wrigley Field]], then known as Weeghman Park, in Chicago. * [[1918]] &ndash; [[World War I]]: The [[Royal Navy|British Royal Navy]] makes a [[Zeebrugge Raid|raid]] in an attempt to neutralise the Belgian [[port of Bruges-Zeebrugge]]. * [[1920]] &ndash; The [[Grand National Assembly of Turkey]] (TBMM) is founded in [[Ankara]]. The assembly denounces the government of [[Sultan]] [[Mehmed VI]] and announces the preparation of a [[Turkish Constitution of 1921|temporary constitution]]. * [[1927]] &ndash; [[Cardiff City F.C.|Cardiff City]] defeat [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] in the [[1927 FA Cup Final|FA Cup Final]], the only time it has been won by a team not based in England. * [[1935]] &ndash; The [[Polish Constitution of 1935]] is adopted. * [[1940]] &ndash; The [[Rhythm Club fire]] at a dance hall in [[Natchez, Mississippi]], kills 198 people. * [[1941]] &ndash; [[World War II]]: The Greek government and [[George II of Greece|King George II]] evacuate [[Athens]] before the invading [[Wehrmacht]]. * [[1942]] &ndash; World War II: [[Baedeker Blitz]]: German bombers hit [[Exeter]], [[Bath, Somerset|Bath]] and [[York]] in retaliation for the British raid on [[Lübeck]]. * [[1945]] &ndash; World War II: [[Adolf Hitler]]'s designated successor, [[Hermann Göring]], sends him a [[Göring Telegram|telegram]] asking permission to take leadership of the [[Third Reich]]. [[Martin Bormann]] and [[Joseph Goebbels]] advise Hitler that the telegram is treasonous. * [[1946]] &ndash; [[Manuel Roxas]] is elected the last President of the [[Commonwealth of the Philippines]]. * [[1949]] &ndash; [[Chinese Civil War]]: Establishment of the [[People's Liberation Army Navy]]. * [[1951]] &ndash; [[Cold War]]: American journalist [[William N. Oatis]] is arrested for espionage by the [[Communist]] government of [[Czechoslovakia]]. * [[1961]] &ndash; [[Algiers putsch of 1961|Algiers putsch]] by French generals. * [[1967]] &ndash; [[Soviet space program]]: [[Soyuz 1]] (Russian: Союз 1, Union 1) a manned spaceflight carrying [[cosmonaut]] Colonel [[Vladimir Komarov]] is launched into orbit. * [[1968]] &ndash; [[Vietnam War]]: Student protesters at [[Columbia University]] in New York City [[Columbia University protests of 1968|take over administration buildings and shut down the university]]. * [[1971]] &ndash; [[Bangladesh Liberation War]]: The Pakistan Army and [[Razakar (Pakistan)|Razakars]] [[Jathibhanga massacre|massacre]] approximately 3,000 Hindu emigrants in the Jathibhanga area of [[East Pakistan]] (now [[Bangladesh]]). * [[1985]] &ndash; [[Coca-Cola]] changes its formula and releases [[New Coke]]. The response is overwhelmingly negative, and the original formula is back on the market in less than three months. * [[1990]] &ndash; [[Namibia]] becomes the 160th [[Member states of the United Nations|member]] of the [[United Nations]] and the 50th [[Member states of the Commonwealth of Nations|member]] of the [[Commonwealth of Nations]]. * [[1993]] &ndash; [[Eritrea]]ns vote overwhelmingly for independence from [[Ethiopia]] in a [[United Nations]]-monitored referendum. * 1993 &ndash; [[Sri Lanka]]n politician [[Lalith Athulathmudali]] is [[Assassination of Lalith Athulathmudali|assassinated]] while addressing a gathering, approximately four weeks ahead of the Provincial Council elections for the [[Western Province, Sri Lanka|Western Province]]. * [[2005]] &ndash; The first ever [[YouTube]] video, titled "[[Me at the zoo]]", was published by user "jawed".<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://time.com/3833222/first-youtube-video/|title=This Is the First Ever YouTube Video|website=Time|access-date=2017-04-22}}</ref> * [[2013]] &ndash; At least 28 people are killed and more than 70 are injured as [[2013 Hawija clashes|violence breaks out]] in [[Hawija]], [[Iraq]]. * [[2018]] &ndash; A [[2018 Toronto van attack|vehicle-ramming attack]] kills 10 people and injures 16 in [[Toronto]]. A 25-year-old suspect, Alek Minassian is arrested.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-43875321|title=Toronto van attack: Suspect quizzed after 10 pedestrians killed|date=24 April 2018|website=BBC|access-date=24 April 2018|}}</ref>
