{{Infobox NRHP | name = Lyric Theater | nrhp_type = cp|nocat=yes | image = LYRIC THEATER, BOONVILLE, COOPER COUNTY, MO.JPG | caption = Lyric Theater, July 2013 | location= NE corner of Main and Vine Sts., [[Boonville, Missouri]] | coordinates = {{coord|38|58|26|N|92|44|33|W|display=inline,title}} | locmapin = Missouri#USA | built = {{Start date|1855}}-1857 | architecture = Greek Revival | added = May 21, 1969 | area = less than one acre | refnum = 69000097<ref name="nris">{{NRISref|version=2010a}}</ref> }} '''Lyric Theater''', also known as the '''Thespian Hall''', a historic [[theatre]] located at [[Boonville, Missouri|Boonville]], [[Cooper County, Missouri]]. It was built in 1855-1857, and is a two-story, rectangular [[Greek Revival architecture|Greek Revival]] style brick building. The front facade features a portico with four unfluted [[Doric order]] columns constructed of wedged shaped brick. The building was enlarged in 1901. When constructed, the basement was originally used as reading room; main floor used as combined theater and lecture hall or auditorium. The second floor housed the city hall, [[Masonic lodge]], and [[Odd Fellows]] hall.<ref name="DNR">{{cite web| url =http://www.dnr.mo.gov/shpo/nps-nr/69000097.pdf| title = National Register of Historic Places Inventory Nomination Form: Lyric Theater| accessdate = 2016-11-01| author=M. Patricia Holmes|format = PDF| date=April 1969|publisher=Missouri Department of Natural Resources}}]</ref>{{rp|2}}
It was listed on the [[National Register of Historic Places]] in 1969.<ref name=nris/> It is located in [[Historic District D]].
