{{Primarysources|date=October 2008}}
The [[Tokyo]] {{Nihongo|'''Wonder Festival'''|ワンダーフェスティバル}}, or {{Nihongo|'''Wonfes'''|ワンフェス|wanfesu}} for short, is a semiannual (Feb, Aug) event held in the [[Makuhari Messe]], in [[Chiba, Chiba|Chiba]], Japan. The main focus is to display and sell "[[garage kit]]s", which are sculptures that usually replicate [[anime]] and game characters, but also popular [[mecha]]/sci-fi characters and creatures such as [[Kuratas]]. These models are extremely detail oriented, and many of these sculptures appear in very small quantities due to the amateur nature of their reproduction. Unusually skilled artisans are promoted specifically during the "wonder showcase" (WSC), in which their works are given special attention and limited quantities of their masterpieces are sold for high prices to avid collectors.<ref>''All 47 Garage Kit Masterpieces Chosen for “Wonder Show Case” in Past Ten Years''. Article series in six parts at gigazine.net:
[http://en.gigazine.net/index.php?/news/comments/20090730_wf2009_s_wsc_001_009/ 1], [http://en.gigazine.net/index.php?/news/comments/20090730_wf2009_s_wsc_010_018/ 2], [http://en.gigazine.net/index.php?/news/comments/20090730_wf2009_s_wsc_019_027/ 3], [http://en.gigazine.net/index.php?/news/comments/20090730_wf2009_s_wsc_028_036/ 4],
[http://en.gigazine.net/index.php?/news/comments/20090730_wf2009_s_wsc_037_045/ 5],
[http://en.gigazine.net/index.php?/news/comments/20090730_wf2009_s_wsc_19th/ 6]</ref> It also showcases future releases by major toy companies.

